HEADWORD: Stitching
<hw>Stitch"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who
stitches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Work done by sewing, esp. when a continuous line of
stitches is shown on the surface; stitches, collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stitchwort</ent>⟦br⟧
